Linux Terminology and Examples

1)Kernel:-
Glue between hardware and applications Example (Linux Kernel)
2)Distributions:-
Collection of a software making up a linux-based OS Example RHLE ubuntu fedora
3)Boot Loader:-
Programm that boots the operating system Example Grub and ISoLinux
4)Service:-
Programm that runs as a background process Example httpd nfsd ntpd
5)Filesystem:
Method for storing and organzing file Example ext3 ext4 FAT NTFS
6)XWindowSystem:
Graphical subsytems on nearly all Linux systems
7)Desktop Environment:-
Graphical User Interface on top of the operating system Example GNOME KDE
8)Command Line Interface:-
Interface for typing commands on top of the operating system
9)Shell:-
takes the commands from cli and instrucuts the operating system Example Bash tcsh zsh
